Posted: Wed Mar 06, 2013 11:28 am
PS. I don't tell other women I like their shoes just to make them like me. I tell them I like their shoes when I actually like their shoes. I say hi to the security guards when I'm leaving, because it's a pleasant ritual that makes me happy. I bring in leftover baked goods because I enjoy sharing things with my office mates.Don't start asking people about their kids just because you need to tick something off on your "I'm a good coworker" checklist. People will sense that you're being disingenuous and they will usually end up disliking you because of it. If you have a complimentary thought about someone, verbalize it (as long as it's work appropriate). If you need to kill time, shoot the breeze with someone. It makes work more pleasant for everyone.I don't say hi to the security guards for any other reason than I like saying hi to them. But I'll tell you that it will definitely not hurt to be friendly with them if I ever get locked out of my office.
