PastorOfMuppets wrote:My career seems to be at a standstill because I suck at / don't play office politics.I have been the technical lead on many projects but frequently my design decisions run up against someone else's prejudices, or who wants my resources who is better at office politics. I try to make my design decisions based on the product constraints and the business needs and keep everything data driven. When arguing a position I stick to the facts and present the data and method the decision was reached. Unfortunately when presented with overwhelming facts, the typical response has been to trash me behind my back to senior management. I then have to justify myself to senior management where they have been told I'm an idiot and don't know what I'm talking about.So what am I doing wrong and how can I improve?If being trashed to senior management for performance, your protection is documentation (at least in any company of any size). Document what you do, how you do, and why. Be able to prove your value. In addition you indicate that you overwhelm people with facts. Perhaps you do not have the ability/skill set to present information to upper management in appropriate bite sized form? Usually, the more senior the person you are presenting to, the less data you are supposed to be showing (the implication being the support data has already been vetted/is accurate).If being trashed for your personality, make sure you look at if they have a point in how you interact with others.
