Quote:In addition you indicate that you overwhelm people with facts. Perhaps you do not have the ability/skill set to present information to upper management in appropriate bite sized form? Usually, the more senior the person you are presenting to, the less data you are supposed to be showing (the implication being the support data has already been vetted/is accurate).“Perfection is achieved perfection not when there is nothing left to add, but when there is nothing left to take away” – Antoine de Saint-ExuperyThis applies perfectly well to reports to upper management. If you review your email/project summary/etc and you think, "That part isn't absolutely necessary..." you still have work to do.
